name: The Heart of Joy
note: We weren't served for 15 minutes and had to listen to a guy composing flute music on the spot (therefore playing strange melodies)

name: Hauber
note: Everything is organic and they have many gluten-free options that don't taste like cardboard. Coffee and pastry portions are very small for the steep price. And saldy not that good.

name: Le Crobag HBF
note: Very expensive. But the pastries are very good, seldom find better ones. There is almost no place to sit. Great for Takeaway

name: Anker HBF
note: Averagely good coffee, nice to sit. They have great food options with a big recommendation for their asian takeaway and the pizza slices, which is amazing.

name: Backwerk
note: Very affordable, has nice seasonal specials. Coffee is kinda bad, but all food is amazing.

name: Lorenzoni
note: Good cakes, relatively nice staff, it is a bit big and therefore uncomfortable.

name: Koller
note: I am biased here for reasons. But 5/5

name: Liebelei
note: Really, really good. But the waitor (owner?) touches women unprompted.
